Solar Pane Monitoring System - API Documentation

Base URL: http://localhost:62889  (or your server's base URL)

1. GET /data
Description: Fetch the latest sensor data representing the system's state.

Response (Example):
{
  "message": "Data fetched successfully.",
  "data": {
    "_id": "60d5ecb8b392cb3a54134102",
    "totalEfficiency": 85.5,
    "power": 350.5,
    "energyTotal": 1500.5,
    "voltage": 24.5,
    "current": 14.3,
    "lightIntensity": 950,
    "panelTemp": 45.2,
    "dustLevel": 12.5,
    "inclinationAngle": 35,
    "panelDirection": "South",
    "sensorHealth": "OK",
    "createdAt": "2023-10-25T10:00:00.000Z",
    "updatedAt": "2023-10-25T10:05:00.000Z",
    "__v": 0
  }
}

--------------------------------------------------

2. POST /data
Description: Create or update the sensor data. Only one row/document is kept for the system's state, acting as a real-time snapshot.

Request Body JSON:
{
  "totalEfficiency": 85.5,
  "power": 350.5,
  "energyTotal": 1500.5,
  "voltage": 24.5,
  "current": 14.3,
  "lightIntensity": 950,
  "panelTemp": 45.2,
  "dustLevel": 12.5,
  "inclinationAngle": 35,
  "panelDirection": "South",
  "sensorHealth": "OK"
}

Response (Example):
{
  "message": "Data created/updated successfully.",
  "data": {
     // Returns the updated JSON object above
  }
}
